28/07/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul returned home from Washington on Sunday (27 July) and said the United States and Turkey will prepare new co-ordinated actions in northern Iraq. As for the US request for Turkey to send peacekeeping troops, Gul said there was no specific timetable and that approval by parliament is necessary. Ankara wants assurances that it would command any troops it dispatches to Iraq.
In other news, Istanbul Mayor Ali Mufit Gurtuna is wrapping up a four-day visit to Macedonia, during which he held talks with government officials and local authorities. His itinerary included stops in Skopje, Ohrid, Tetovo and Gostivar. (Radikal - 28/07/03; Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 27/07/03; MIA, Makfax - 25/07/03)
